Thomas,

JUnit 4&#39;s extension mechanism is very different from JUnit 3&#39;s.  Probably,
to do what you want would require a new custom runner.  Where is the
information on how long each timeout should be coming from?  Thanks,

   David Saff

On 4/1/07, Thomas L Roche &lt;tlroche@...&gt; wrote:
&gt;
&gt; Has someone successfully used JUnitPerf with JUnit4 test classes?
&gt; If so, please post example(s), either here or on
&gt;
&gt; http://tech.groups.yahoo.com/group/junitperf/messages
&gt;
&gt; Why I ask (and ask here):
&gt;
&gt; I have a test framework developed with JUnit 3.8.x that uses JUnitPerf
&gt; TimedTest&#39;s. It needed refactoring, and I could see how a cleaner
&gt; refactoring could be done without extends TestCase. Unfortunately
&gt;
&gt; * JUnit4&#39;s timeout requires a constant expression, and I want (and do)
&gt;   get the timeout value dynamically.
&gt;
&gt; * I want my tests to be runnable within a third framework (PDE Build)
&gt;   which I know supports JUnit3 tests, I am told (by someone I trust)
&gt;   supports JUnit4 tests, and I don&#39;t know supports TestNG tests.
&gt;   &lt;aside&gt;Information about TestNG/PDEBuild-integration appreciated.
&gt;   &lt;/aside&gt;
&gt;
&gt; So I relinked my framework with the JUnit 4.1 JAR and twiddled it
&gt; (e.g. annotated, twiddled imports and asserts &lt;aside&gt;anybody got
&gt; pointer(s) to JUnit3-&gt;JUnit4 migration automation? &lt;/aside&gt;) and the
&gt; good news was, it ran! but the bad news was, it wouldn&#39;t time out ...
&gt;
&gt; I tried a few different things which I unfortunately did not record in
&gt; the heat of the moment--definitely JUnit4TestAdapter and @RunWith(
&gt; Suite.class)--but could not make the @#$%^&! thing timeout. So I
&gt; posted the JUnitPerf list
&gt;
&gt; http://tech.groups.yahoo.com/group/junitperf/message/86
&gt;
&gt; because it seemed to be the place to ask (am I missing something?)
&gt; despite the fact that Mike Clark hasn&#39;t posted there in over a year.
&gt; The next day, someone else posted a similar question
&gt;
&gt; http://tech.groups.yahoo.com/group/junitperf/message/87
&gt;
&gt; though asking about LoadTest as well. So if you&#39;ve got examples of how
&gt; to run a LoadTest or TimedTest (especially the latter :-) under
&gt; JUnit4, please reply to me, to junit@yahoogroups.com, to
